    698          /**
    699           *    @brief    This method writes data from "source" (buffer address mentioned by the Application)
    700           *              to the "destination" (Transmitter FIFO) as per the size mentioned to the specific Spi and also
    701           *              returns the response for the write operation.
    702           *    @details  The data in the Transmitter FIFO is sent to other Spi node through the specified Spi COM port
    703           *              whenever the Transmitter is free. Before writing into the Transmitter FIFO check for the
    704           *              FIFO availability using Spi__GetStatus() API to avoid the over writing on the existing data.
    705           *    @param    spi  : specific Spi device
    706           *    @param    buf  : source buffer from where the data to be sent
    707           *    @param    size : defines the amount of data to be sent
