   1160          /**
   1161           *  @brief      Reconfigure a specific Spi for a customised setting
   1162           *
   1163           *  @details    This function changes the configureation of a specific SPI and must called after the Spi has being initialzie
   1164           *              Every time that the Spi is initialized it starts with the default parameters
   1165           *
   1166           *  @param      spi the specific spi device
   1167           *  @param      pol defines the polarity of SCK signal
   1168           *  @param      edge defines the the edge of action for the SCK line
   1169           *  @param      order defines if the MSB bit goes first or the LSB bit goes first
